  <!-- Applications -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim bg-dots" aria-labelledby="apps-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Applications</div>
      <h2 id="apps-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Chain Conveyor <span class="text-accent">Applications</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p><strong class="text-ink">Automotive paint and assembly:</strong> <a href="/conveyor-types/chain-conveyors/overhead/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Overhead power-and-free conveyors</a> carry car bodies through paint prep, e-coat, primer, topcoat, and bake oven processes. The power-and-free design allows bodies to accumulate at different stages, switch to spur lines for rework, and travel at different speeds through different zones. This is the highest-value chain conveyor application in manufacturing.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Bulk material transport:</strong> <a href="/conveyor-types/drag-chain-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Drag chain conveyors</a> move grain, cement, ash, and chemical powders between storage, processing, and packaging equipment. The enclosed trough contains dust and prevents contamination. Drag chain conveyors feed <a href="/conveyor-types/bucket-elevators/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">bucket elevators</a>, mixers, and packaging machines in food and chemical plants.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Pallet and heavy-load transport:</strong> Slat chain conveyors carry pallets, engine blocks, and heavy assemblies through manufacturing processes. The rigid slat surface supports concentrated point loads that would damage belts and derail rollers. Slat chain conveyors feed welding stations, machining cells, and <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/pallet/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">pallet wrapping stations</a>.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Garment and textile handling:</strong> Overhead monorail conveyors carry garments on hangers through sorting, pressing, and shipping operations. The garments hang freely, preventing wrinkles and allowing visual inspection during transport. Garment-on-hanger (GOH) conveyors are specialized overhead chain systems used in apparel distribution centers and dry cleaning plants.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Food packaging lines:</strong> Plastic table-top chain conveyors carry bottles, cans, and cartons through <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">food packaging lines</a>. The sanitary plastic chain withstands washdown, and the modular design handles curves and elevation changes without transfer points that could cause jams or contamination. Beverage filling and packaging lines use table-top chain as the primary transport between filler, capper, labeler, and case packer.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Mining and aggregate:</strong> Apron chain feeders and conveyors handle the heaviest, most abrasive materials: crushed rock, ore, coal, and clinker. They receive material from primary crushers and feed secondary processing at controlled rates. Apron conveyors also handle <a href="/conveyor-types/screw-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">screw conveyor</a> and <a href="/conveyor-types/bucket-elevators/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">bucket elevator</a> feed in heavy industrial plants.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
